body:
I've recently tried to update to 2.4.4 (from 2.4.3) and faced a curious error on form submission:

```
2015-11-23 08:10:08,670 [error] p.c.s.n.PlayDefaultUpstreamHandler : 
  Cannot invoke the action
play.api.PlayException: Invalid forwarded header[Forwarding header '::1' supplied by trusted proxy
ConnectionInfo(/127.0.0.1,false) could not be parsed: failure: string matching regex `_[\p{Alnum}\._-]+' expected but `:' found: fix proxy header or
remove proxy from play.http.forwarded.trustedProxies config entry]
    at play.core.server.common.ForwardedHeaderHandler.scan$1(ForwardedHeaderHandler.scala:93) ~[play-server_2.11-2.4.4.jar:2.4.4]
    at play.core.server.common.ForwardedHeaderHandler.remoteConnection(ForwardedHeaderHandler.scala:116) ~[play-server_2.11-2.4.4.jar:2.4.4]
    at play.core.server.common.ForwardedHeaderHandler.remoteConnection(ForwardedHeaderHandler.scala:57) ~[play-server_2.11-2.4.4.jar:2.4.4]
    at play.core.server.netty.PlayDefaultUpstreamHandler$$anon$1.remoteConnection$lzycompute(PlayDefaultUpstreamHandler.scala:111) ~[play-netty-server_2.11-2.4.4.jar:2.4.4]
    at play.core.server.netty.PlayDefaultUpstreamHandler$$anon$1.remoteConnection(PlayDefaultUpstreamHandler.scala:108) ~[play-netty-server_2.11-2.4.4.jar:2.4.4]
```

The application is running behind a nginx, which is configured like:

```
upstream application1 {
    server localhost:8999;
}
server {
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://application1;
        proxy_redirect off;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header Host $http_host;
        add_header X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN;
    }
    # Some more detailed stuff which is not relevant here.
}
```

This error did **not** occur on 2.4.3, and only affects POST requests on form submission. All other POST or GET requests work fine.
